    "intro": "Interpretation moves from observation — what does the text say — to discerning the author's intent in its original context and its place in the larger canonical story. 2 Samuel 18 sits at the intersection of political history, family tragedy, and covenantal theology. The movements below trace the chapter's argument from its military opening through its pastoral close, attending to what the Deuteronomistic narrator intends, what the characters reveal about themselves, and how the chapter contributes to the theology of kingship, fatherhood, and divine judgment in the Succession Narrative.",
